name: Viewed by senior manager of site
ALL INCOMING MATERIALS - CEMENT / FLYASH & ADMIXTURES
FOR_001 & FOR_002:. Number of test certificates checked
* Minimum: 1 check / quarter / type / supplier and for any new supply,
eg. 2 cement types & 1 flyash in use, 1 new cement - Required No. = 4 (per quarter)
* Minimum 1 inspection / week / type / supplier, eg. 2 coarse aggregate types - Required No. = 8
FOR_005: Number of aggregate grading checks
* Minimum: 1 check / quarter / type / supplier and for any new supply,
eg. 2 coarse aggregate types in use, 1 new - Required No. = 3 (per quarter)
* Minimum: 1 inspection / week / type / supplier, eg. 2 fine aggregate types - Required No. = 8
FOR_006: Number of aggregate grading, fineness and colour checks
* Minimum: 1 check / quarter / type / supplier and for any new supply,
eg. 2 fine aggregate types in use, 1 new - Required No. = 3 (per quarter)
FOR_007 & FOR_008: Number of reinforcement deliveries inspected
Date of last annual UTS testing:
FOR_009: Number of fittings deliveries inspected
Is the calibration of all equipment current?
If No please comment (eg. Equipment out of service):
Equipment requiring calibration may include external load tester, stressing jacks, compressive cylinder test machine, pressure gauges & weigh scales.
FOR_010: Number of secondary reinforcement pole cage inspections
* Minimum: 1st cage of new size/production run
THEN 1/size/type/day OR 1in5 but not less than 1/week
eg. 100 same size reinforcement cages made for the month over 20 production days - Required No. = 20 OR 4
FOR_011: Number of primary reinforcement pole cage inspections
* Minimum: 1st cage of new size/production run
THEN 1/size/type/day OR 1in5 but not less than 1/week
eg. 100 same size reinforcement cages made for the month over 20 production days - Required No. = 20 OR 4
FOR_014: Number of assembled pole mould inspections
* Minimum: 1st mould of new production run THEN 3 moulds/shift eg. 20 shifts for production area - Required No. = 60
* Minimum: TIGHTENED - weekly each machine centre REDUCED - monthly each machine centre.
eg. 3 machine centres all on reduced mode – Required No. = 3
FOR_022: Number of poles checked for dimensional tolerance
* Minimum: 1st pole from new mould then 1/size/day
eg. 2 pole sizes produced over entire month (20 production days) Required No. = 40
FOR_023: Number of pole ultimate or type tests
* Minimum: Type tests - new or major design alteration Ultimate - as detailed in specification.
FOR_024: Number of pole batch tests
Batch > 25 - 1in50 not less than 1 Batch < 25 - 1in50 of mixed batch
eg. For month, Mixed batches < 25, totalling 150 - Required No. = 3
FOR_025: Number of poles tested for cover to steel
* Minimum: Initial Prototype test then 1in 500 of those tested to ultimate load
FOR_010: Number of secondary reinforcement pole cage inspections
* Minimum: 1st cage of new size/production run
THEN 1/size/type/day OR 1in5 but not less than 1/week
eg. 100 same size reinforcement cages made for the month over 20 production days - Required No. = 20 OR 4
FOR_011: Number of primary reinforcement pole cage inspections
* Minimum: 1st cage of new size/production run
THEN 1/size/type/day OR 1in5 but not less than 1/week
eg. 100 same size reinforcement cages made for the month over 20 production days - Required No. = 20 OR 4
FOR_014: Number of assembled pile mould inspections
* Minimum: 1st mould of new production run THEN 3 moulds/shift
eg. 20 shifts for production area - Required No. = 60
FOR_030: Number of assembled mould (pile toe) inspections
* Minimum: 1st mould of new production run THEN 1 moulds/week/size
eg. 2 sizes made continuously for month - Required No. = 8
* Minimum: TIGHTENED - weekly each machine centre
eg. 3 machine centres all on reduced mode – Required No. = 3
FOR_033 Number of piles checked for dimensional tolerance
eg. 3 sizes made over 20 production days for month - Required No. = 60
